Commentary Text: Hardik Pandya to Parthiv Patel, out Caught by Suryakumar Yadav!! What a soft dismissal! For all the shots he's played so far, Parthiv departs in tame fashion. It's been the story of his IPL career by and large. Gets attractive starts but perishes after the Powerplay. This was a cleverly bowled off cutter from Hardik and Parthiv wanted to go aerial through his favorite region square through the off-side. Misread the pace and ended up chipping it straight to Yadav at backward point. Parthiv Patel c Suryakumar Yadav b Hardik Pandya 28(20) [4s-4 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Behrendorff to Kohli, out Caught by de Kock!! Body blow by Behrendorff! Cracking delivery and Kohli has been sent back early. Was angling across from a good length around off, held its line after pitching and bounced just a bit more than Kohli anticipated it to. He was looking to force it through the off-side and got cramped, thereby getting an inside edge through to de Kock who took it with ease. Just the kind of start MI were looking for. Kohli c de Kock b Behrendorff 8(9) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Navdeep Saini to Hardik Pandya, no run, please take a close look at the length, it's back of a length again, the most under-rated length at the death. Pandya moved across and wanted to slog over mid-wicket, missed it. People keep trying the yorker and miss their lengths, margin of error is so less when compared to the back of a length balls. You may still get hit, but the batsman has to do that much more to get runs
